{"source_key":"sha256-ea08d35f42d5530fbe92c80d4f5b27e9","record_index":138,"record_hash":"sha256:e85b1d6ad21b1c40875f8486ae1104e8fd5139aa7fa80a7ef8d32b0d0df173a3","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:29:26.360Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 40057e\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2622\nOutput:\n# GitButler Cloud Implementation Plan\n\nGitButler Cloud is a private per-user sync, backup, and takeover service for\nGitButler work. A user approves a local or headless client through a browser,\nthe client receives a revocable token, and each approved machine syncs Git refs\nto a private code.storage-backed repository.\n\nThe source writeup is `but-sync.md`. There is no `git-cloud.md` file in this\nrepo.\n\n## Goals\n\nIn scope for v0:\n\n1. Browser signup/login with cookie sessions.\n2. CLI device login for `but-login`, including remote/headless approval.\n3. Per-user, per-client cloud tokens that can be revoked from the web UI.\n4. Cloud project resolution and automatic backing repository creation.\n5. Git Smart HTTP proxying to code.storage for cloud projects.\n6. Rust CLI binaries:\n   - `but-login`\n   - `but-sync`\n   - `but-cloud clients`\n   - `but-cloud branches`\n   - `but-takeover`\n7. Ref synchronization across client namespaces:\n   - local branches to `refs/<client_id>/heads/*`\n   - Git metadata refs to `refs/<client_id>/meta/*`\n   - remote client refs fetched to `refs/gitbutler/cloud/<client_id>/*`\n\nOut of scope for v0: orgs, shared teams, public branch URLs, OAuth providers,\nbilling, SSH transport, web code browsing, and per-branch share permissions.\n\n## System Shape\n\nThe implementation has two parts:\n\n- Next.js server app with Drizzle/PlanetScale MySQL, cookie auth, device auth APIs, token\n  storage, cloud project APIs, and streaming Git proxy routes.\n- Rust workspace with one crate, `but-cloud-cli`, producing top-level\n  `but-login`, `but-sync`, `but-cloud`, and `but-takeover` binaries.\n\nConfiguration:\n\n```env\nDATABASE_HOST=\"aws.connect.psdb.cloud/gitbutler_dev\"\nDATABASE_USERNAME=\"<planetscale username>\"\nDATABASE_PASSWORD=\"<planetscale password>\"\nSESSION_SECRET=\"<random 32+ bytes>\"\nPIERRE_ORG_NAME=\"your-org\"\nPIERRE_PRIVATE_KEY=\"<PKCS8 PEM>\"\nBOWTIE_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=\"http://localhost:3000\"\n```\n\nThe private key \n[TRUNCATED]\neover <client>/<branch>`:\n\n1. Resolves the current cloud project and fetches cloud refs.\n2. Verifies `refs/gitbutler/cloud/<client>/heads/<branch>` exists.\n3. Always stashes dirty and untracked work before changing the workspace.\n4. Reads `but status --json`, then unapplies every active branch except the target.\n5. Aborts if the target branch is active in a multi-head stack, because unapplying a sibling would unapply the target stack too.\n6. Applies the existing target branch or creates it from the selected cloud ref.\n7. Preserves local-only commits and runs `but pick <commit> <branch>` for cloud-only commits in oldest-first order.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Remote URL normalization treats common HTTPS and `git@host:path.git` forms as\n  the same project identity.\n- The v0 CLI stores credentials in a JSON file under the platform config\n  directory. Native keychain storage can be added later behind the same config\n  helper.\n- GitButler's operations log head currently lives in\n  `.git/gitbutler/operations-log.toml`, not in a Git ref, so v0 does not transfer\n  the operations log as part of `but-sync`.\n- The cloud proxy cannot cheaply inspect Git receive-pack contents without\n  buffering/parsing pack protocol, so namespace enforcement is expressed through\n  server-returned CLI refspecs in v0. A later hardened version should validate\n  receive-pack commands before forwarding writes.\n- All Git proxy route handlers must stay on the Node runtime and preserve Git\n  Smart HTTP content types.\n\n## Verification\n\nServer:\n\n```bash\npnpm drizzle:push\npnpm exec tsc --noEmit\n```\n\nRust CLI:\n\n```bash\ncargo build -p but-cloud-cli\n```\n\nEnd-to-end smoke path:\n\n1. Start the web server.\n2. Run `but-login --server http://localhost:3000`.\n3. Approve the device in the browser.\n4. Run `but-sync` in a Git repository.\n5. Run `but-sync` from a second checkout.\n6. Confirm incoming refs appear under `refs/gitbutler/cloud/<client_id>/*`.\n7. Run `but-takeover <client_id>/<branch>` and confirm the local branch is\n   created from the cloud ref.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:29:26.360Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}